(2888, 'Choose <code>item_id</code> Parameter Value', 'GA4_ANALYTICS_ITEM_ID_VALUE', 'products_model', '<br>When products are included in GA4 events, what value should be used for the <code>item_id</code> parameter?  If you choose <code>products_id</code>, the product\'s model (if that value is not empty) is placed into the field name you identify below. Default: <code>products_model</code>.', 163, 25, '2024-07-30 11:42:46', '2024-05-03 10:58:36', NULL, 'zen_cfg_select_option([\'products_model\', \'products_id\'],'),
(2889, 'Debug Mode, IP List', 'GA4_ANALYTICS_DEBUG_IP_LIST', '', 'If you want to enable <em>Debug Mode</em> for only certain IP addresses, enter those IP addresses here, using a comma-separated list (intervening spaces are OK).  Leave this field empty (the default) and the <em>Debug Mode</em> applies to <b>all</b> IP addresses.<br>', 163, 505, NULL, '2024-05-03 10:58:36', NULL, NULL),
(2890, 'Choose <code>products_model</code> Field Name', 'GA4_ANALYTICS_ITEM_MODEL_FIELD', 'ep.item_model', 'If you chose <code>products_id</code> for the setting above, identify the name of the event field into which the <code>products_model</code> should be placed.  The default (<code>ep.item_model</code>) might be &quot;difficult&quot; to see in your Google Management Console.  Some alternate suggestions, reusing built-in GA4 fields are <code>item_list_id</code> and <code>item_list_name</code>.<br>', 163, 30, NULL, '2024-05-03 10:58:36', NULL, NULL),
